abstract: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
snippet: They said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”
lead_paragraph: The Democratic presidential candidates have been responding this afternoon to the thing they all knew was coming: the Senate’s acquittal of President Trump. And they all said what was, essentially, the only thing they could say: “Voters, please do what the Senate didn’t.”

abstract: He held a fund-raiser in Summit, N.J., early Wednesday afternoon and was planning two in New York: one Wednesday night and one Thursday morning.
snippet: He held a fund-raiser in Summit, N.J., early Wednesday afternoon and was planning two in New York: one Wednesday night and one Thursday morning.
lead_paragraph: Former Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., who appears headed toward a first- or second-place finish in the Iowa caucuses based on partial results, is taking a break from his victory lap to raise money.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders are nearly tied in the Iowa Democratic caucuses, with nearly all results counted in a contest marred by technical issues and reporting delays.
snippet: Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders are nearly tied in the Iowa Democratic caucuses, with nearly all results counted in a contest marred by technical issues and reporting delays.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders are nearly tied in the Iowa Democratic caucuses, with nearly all results counted in a contest marred by technical issues and reporting delays.
headline_main: Buttigieg, Sanders Nearly Tied as Iowa Caucus Results Narrow

abstract: The Iowa Democratic Party has released another batch of results from Monday’s caucuses, but the new data did little to change the positioning of the top candidates.
lead_paragraph: The Iowa Democratic Party has released another batch of results from Monday’s caucuses, but the new data did little to change the positioning of the top candidates.
headline_main: Iowa Democrats release a new batch of results.

abstract: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
snippet: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Maybe it was the threat of bad weather. Maybe it was a seating assignment debacle. Maybe it was a struggling campaign organization that still hadn’t found its footing.

abstract: Pete Buttigieg led in Iowa's initial caucus results with 62% of precincts reporting, with U.S. Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren in second and third place and former Vice President Joe Biden trailing in fourth, the Iowa Democratic Party reported on Tuesday.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Pete Buttigieg led in Iowa's initial caucus results with 62% of precincts reporting, with U.S. Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren in second and third place and former Vice President Joe Biden trailing in fourth, the Iowa Democratic Party reported on Tuesday.
